Employee Management System Documentation
This document provides complete technical documentation for the Employee Management System developed using React.js, Node.js, Express.js and MongoDB.


Project Overview
The system provides JWT authentication, role-based access control (Super Admin, HR Manager, Employee), employee management, attendance, leave management, payroll, dashboard and organization hierarchy.
Technology Stack
Frontend: React.js, React Router, Axios
Backend: Node.js, Express.js
Database: MongoDB with Mongoose
Authentication: JWT + bcryptjs
Features
• Secure Login/Logout
• Protected Routes
• Role Based Access Control
• Employee CRUD
• Dashboard Statistics
• Attendance Management
• Leave Management
• Payroll Management
• Organization Hierarchy
• Soft Delete
• Search, Filter and Pagination
Architecture
React Frontend -> Express REST API -> MongoDB.
JWT token is stored after login and sent in Authorization header.
Authentication
Login verifies bcrypt password, issues JWT. Logout clears local storage. Protected APIs require Bearer token.
Roles
Super Admin: Full access.
HR Manager: Manage employees except Super Admin restrictions.
Employee: Manage own profile, attendance, leave and view own payroll.
Modules
Dashboard, Employees, Attendance, Leave, Payroll, Organization, Profile.
API Summary
Implemented REST APIs for authentication, dashboard, employees, attendance, leave, payroll and organization hierarchy.
Validation & Security
Backend and frontend validation, password hashing, JWT authentication, authorization middleware, soft delete, circular reporting prevention.
Installation
1. npm install in backend and frontend.
2. Configure .env with MONGO_URI, JWT_SECRET and PORT.
3. Start backend using npm start.
4. Start frontend using npm start.
Demo Login
Use the credentials configured in your MongoDB database. Example:
Email: admin@gmail.com
Password: Admin@123
Update these values if your seeded database uses different credentials.
Reviewer Guide
Run backend and frontend, login, verify dashboard, employee CRUD, attendance, leave, organization hierarchy, RBAC and protected routes.
Limitations
Bonus features such as Docker, CSV import, unit tests and deployment are not included.
Future Improvements
Add Docker, unit tests, CSV import, dashboard charts, email notifications and deployment.


## 1. Overview

The Employee Management System is a full-stack web application for managing employees, attendance, leave requests, payroll, and organizational reporting structure. The system uses JWT-based authentication, bcrypt password hashing, MongoDB persistence, and role-based access control.

The application is divided into two main parts:

- `frontend/` - React application
- `backend/` - Node.js, Express, and MongoDB API

## 2. System Architecture

```text
React Frontend
  |
  | Axios HTTP requests
  v
Express REST API
  |
  | Mongoose ODM
  v
MongoDB Database
```

Authentication uses JWT tokens. After successful login, the frontend stores the token and attaches it to protected API calls using the Authorization header.

## 3. Authentication

### Login Flow

1. User submits email and password.
2. Frontend sends credentials to `POST /api/auth/login`.
3. Backend checks the user by email.
4. Backend compares the password using bcrypt.
5. Backend returns a signed JWT and user details.
6. Frontend stores token and user details in `localStorage`.
7. Protected routes become accessible.

### Logout Flow

1. Frontend removes token and user data from `localStorage`.
2. User is redirected to the login page.

### Protected Routes

Frontend protected pages are wrapped with `ProtectedRoute`. Backend protected APIs use the `authenticate` middleware.

## 4. Role-Based Access Control

The system supports three roles:

```text
Super Admin
HR Manager
Employee
```

### Super Admin Permissions

- View dashboard statistics
- Create employees
- Edit employees
- Soft delete employees
- Assign reporting managers
- View organization tree
- View direct reportees
- Approve and reject leave requests
- Generate payroll
- Mark payroll as paid

### HR Manager Permissions

- View dashboard statistics
- Create employees
- Edit employees
- Soft delete employees, with Super Admin restrictions handled by backend logic
- View organization tree
- View direct reportees
- Approve and reject leave requests
- Generate payroll
- Mark payroll as paid

### Employee Permissions

- Login
- View protected app pages
- View own profile
- Update own profile where allowed
- Check in and check out
- View own attendance
- Apply for leave
- View own leave records
- View own payroll records

## 5. Database Models

### User

Collection model: `User`

Fields:

- `employeeId` - unique employee code
- `name` - employee full name
- `email` - unique login email
- `password` - hashed password
- `phone` - phone number
- `department` - department name
- `designation` - job title
- `salary` - salary amount
- `joiningDate` - date of joining
- `status` - `Active` or `Inactive`
- `role` - `Super Admin`, `HR Manager`, or `Employee`
- `manager` - reporting manager user ID
- `profileImage` - uploaded profile image path
- `isDeleted` - soft delete flag
- `createdAt` and `updatedAt`

Important behavior:

- Passwords are hashed in a Mongoose `pre("save")` hook.
- Deleted employees remain in MongoDB with `isDeleted: true`.

### Attendance

Collection model: `Attendance`

Fields:

- `employee` - user reference
- `date` - attendance date
- `month` - numeric month
- `year` - numeric year
- `checkIn` - check-in time
- `checkOut` - check-out time
- `workingHours` - calculated hours
- `status` - `Present`, `Absent`, `Half Day`, or `Late`
- `remarks`
- `createdAt` and `updatedAt`

Important behavior:

- One attendance record is allowed per employee per day.
- Late status is assigned when check-in is after office start time.
- Half day status can be assigned based on checkout working hours.

### Leave

Collection model: `Leave`

Fields:

- `employee` - user reference
- `leaveType` - `Casual`, `Sick`, `Earned`, `Maternity`, `Paternity`, or `Loss of Pay`
- `startDate`
- `endDate`
- `totalDays`
- `reason`
- `status` - `Pending`, `Approved`, or `Rejected`
- `approvedBy` - approver user reference
- `remarks`
- `createdAt` and `updatedAt`

Important behavior:

- Leave cannot be applied for past dates.
- End date cannot be before start date.
- Overlapping pending or approved leave requests are blocked.

### Payroll

Collection model: `Payroll`

Fields:

- `employee` - user reference
- `month`
- `year`
- `basicSalary`
- `bonus`
- `deductions`
- `tax`
- `netSalary`
- `paymentStatus` - `Pending` or `Paid`
- `paymentDate`
- `createdAt` and `updatedAt`

Important behavior:

- Duplicate payroll records for the same employee, month, and year are blocked.
- Payroll generation uses attendance data to calculate salary impact.

## 6. API Documentation

Base URL:

```text
http://localhost:5000/api
```

Protected endpoints require:

```text
Authorization: Bearer <token>
```

### Auth APIs

#### POST `/auth/login`

Logs in a user.

Request:

```json
{
  "email": "admin@gmail.com",
  "password": "Admin@123"
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Login Successful",
  "token": "jwt_token",
  "user": {
    "id": "user_id",
    "name": "Super Admin",
    "email": "admin@gmail.com",
    "role": "Super Admin"
  }
}
```

#### GET `/auth/profile`

Returns the logged-in user profile.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee

### Employee APIs

#### POST `/employees`

Creates an employee.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

Request:

```json
{
  "employeeId": "EMP002",
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "Password@123",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "department": "IT",
  "designation": "Developer",
  "salary": 50000,
  "joiningDate": "2026-07-19",
  "role": "Employee",
  "manager": "manager_user_id"
}
```

#### GET `/employees`

Returns employees with pagination, search, and filters.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee

Query parameters:

- `page`
- `limit`
- `search`
- `department`
- `role`
- `status`
- `sortBy`
- `order`

Example:

```text
GET /api/employees?search=john&department=IT&role=Employee&status=Active
```

#### GET `/employees/:id`

Returns one employee by ID.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee can view own profile only

#### PUT `/employees/:id`

Updates an employee.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee can update own profile only

#### DELETE `/employees/:id`

Soft deletes an employee.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

#### PUT `/employees/:id/upload-profile`

Uploads a profile image.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee can upload own profile image

Content type:

```text
multipart/form-data
```

Field:

```text
profileImage
```

#### PATCH `/employees/:id/manager`

Assigns reporting manager.

Access:

- Super Admin

Request:

```json
{
  "manager": "manager_user_id"
}
```

#### GET `/employees/:id/reportees`

Returns direct reportees for an employee.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

### Dashboard APIs

#### GET `/dashboard/stats`

Returns employee summary statistics.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

Response includes:

- Total employees
- Active employees
- Inactive employees
- HR manager count
- Recent employees

#### GET `/dashboard/departments`

Returns department-wise employee count.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

#### GET `/dashboard/hierarchy`

Returns manager and employee hierarchy data.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

### Organization APIs

#### GET `/organization/tree`

Returns organization hierarchy tree.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

#### GET `/organization/reportees/:id`

Returns direct reportees.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager

#### PATCH `/organization/manager/:id`

Assigns reporting manager.

Access:

- Super Admin

Request:

```json
{
  "manager": "manager_user_id"
}
```

### Leave APIs

#### POST `/leaves/apply`

Applies for leave.

Access:

- Super Admin
- HR Manager
- Employee

Request:

```json
